data.title: German Masters of The 19thcentury
data.meta_description: German Masters of the 19thCentury - Free ebook download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read book online for free. This document provides an introduction to the exhibition "German Masters of the Nineteeth Century: Paintings and Drawings from the Federal Republic of Germany". It was published as the catalogue for an exhibition held at The Metropolitan Museum of Art in New York from May to July 1981 and later at the Art Gallery of Ontario from August to October 1981. The exhibition featured works by major German artists from the 19th century representing the main artistic movements of the period: Romanticism, the Nazarenes, Idealism, Realism, and Impressionism. The catalogue includes essays, entries on each work, biographies of the artists, and a bibliography. It serves as an important introduction to German painting during this influential period.
